### Hero Slice (`slices/Hero/index.tsx`)

The Hero slice demonstrates proper usage of all color variables:

```tsx
// Section background
<section className="bg-[var(--color-background)]">

// Title text
<div className="text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">

// Description text
<div className="text-[var(--color-text-secondary)]">

// Primary button
<a className="text-[var(--color-button-primary-text)] bg-[var(--color-button-primary-bg)] border border-[var(--color-button-primary-bg)]">

// Secondary button
<a className="text-[var(--color-button-secondary-text)] bg-[var(--color-button-secondary-bg)] border border-[var(--color-button-secondary-border)]">
```

### Homepage (`app/page.tsx`)

The homepage shows how to layer backgrounds:

```tsx
// Outer container with page background
<div className="bg-[var(--color-background)]">

// Inner card with surface background
<main className="bg-[var(--color-surface)]">

// Heading
<h1 className="text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">

// Body text
<p className="text-[var(--color-text-secondary)]">
```

## Rules

1. **Never use hardcoded colors** - Always use CSS variables
2. **Never use Tailwind color classes** - Avoid `text-gray-600`, `bg-black`, etc.
3. **Never use dark: variants** - The variables handle light/dark mode automatically
4. **Use semantic variables** - Choose the variable that matches the purpose (e.g., `--color-text-secondary` for body text, not `--brand-primary`)

## For AI Agents: Updating the Color Scheme

To update the site's colors from Brand.dev output, only modify `app/globals.css`:

1. Set `--brand-primary`, `--brand-secondary`, `--brand-accent` from `brand.colors` array
2. Determine if the target site is light or dark mode
3. Set semantic colors accordingly:

**Light mode values:**

- `--color-background: #ffffff`
- `--color-surface: #f9fafb`
- `--color-text-primary: #171717`
- `--color-text-secondary: #6b7280`
- `--color-border: #e5e7eb`

**Dark mode values:**

- `--color-background: #0a0a0a`
- `--color-surface: #171717`
- `--color-text-primary: #f9fafb`
- `--color-text-secondary: #a1a1aa`
- `--color-border: #27272a`

4. Ensure button text has sufficient contrast with button background
